{
  "texts": [
    "The minimal prior means that the model ensemble tends to include a diversity of models degenerate with respect to the observables.",
    "Hence the inferred uncertainties are generally larger than in other techniques.",
    "The reconstruction of Abell 2744 by Sebesta et al. (2019) is illustrative.",
    "Since galaxy lenses provide much less data than cluster lenses, a more informative prior p(κ) is necessary.",
    "An explicit but still very weak prior (amounting to requiring the lens to be centrally concentrated) has been used in several modeling codes (Williams and Saha 2000; Saha and Williams 2004; Coles et al. 2014; Küng 2018)."
  ]
}